  "description": "## The Sunken Temple of Omu\n\nA three-level temple built into a limestone cave system beneath the Chult jungle. The temple features ancient chulan architecture with serpent motifs throughout.\n\n### Level 1: Outer Chambers\n- **Main Entrance** (cells 14,2-16,2): Stone steps leading down, guarded by giant scorpions\n- **Guard Room** (cells 4,4-8,8): Where yuan-ti cultists rotate shifts\n- **Prison Cells** (cells 20,4-24,8): Where captured villagers are held\n- **Vexia's Cell** (cells 22,6-23,7): Near the prison cells\n\n### Level 2: Inner Chambers\n- **Ritual Chamber** (cells 10,14-18,18): Altars and ritual components\n- **Treasure Vault** (cells 4,14-8,18): Heavily trapped, contains the Serpent's Heart\n- **Cultist Quarters** (cells 20,14-24,18): Where cultists rest\n- **Sssira's Chamber** (cells 22,16-23,17): High priestess's quarters\n\n### Level 3: Inner Sanctum\n- **Kethis's Sanctum** (cells 12,24-18,28): Ritual altar and serpent portal\n- **Serpent Garden** (cells 4,24-8,28): Chamber filled with living serpents\n- **Ancient Murals** (cells 20,24-24,28): Depict chulan history\n\n### Stairs\n- **Level 1 to Level 2** (cells 14,10-16,10): Central staircase\n- **Level 2 to Level 3** (cells 14,20-16,20): Central staircase\n",
  "displayName": "Sunken Temple"
